        <section class="bio-section">
            <h2>About the Artist</h2>
            <p>
                Anita Magsaysay-Ho (1914–2012) was a Filipino painter and the only female member of the 
                "Thirteen Moderns," a group of artists who helped pioneer modern art in the Philippines. 
                She is best known for her stylized depictions of Filipina women performing everyday 
                tasks, characterized by gentle movements and luminous colors.
            </p>
